parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the camshaft position sensor can cause the check engine light to come on, leading to potential engine damage, stalling, or even engine fires, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on intermittently
the engine light stays on for an extended period
the engine smokes
the vehicle stalls
or the vehicle has difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inability to obtain recall repairs can lead to continued exposure to safety risks, including engine damage, stalling, or even engine fires, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Dealerships do not have parts available
dealerships refuse to honor the recall
dealerships are not in operation
or there are no authorized service centers in the area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hose can cause brake fluid leakage, leading to loss of vehicle braking, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the camshaft position sensor can cause the check engine light to come on, and the vehicle may stop running, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Check engine light comes on
vehicle stops running
engine stalling
engine misfire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inability to honor recalls can lead to unresolved safety issues, putting drivers and passengers at risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Dealership unable to perform recall
no parts available
